Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.13,0:00:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial through your user
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.49,0:00:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, there's a lot that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.36,0:00:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,people experience in addition to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.06,0:00:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,your game's gameplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.82,0:00:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the next few minutes, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.08,0:00:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,going to cover 10 design tips to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.21,0:00:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,create great experiences as soon
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.16,0:00:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as someone taps your app icon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these tips can be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.25,0:00:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,applied to apps that are looking
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.83,0:00:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to be just as immersive,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.37,0:00:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,engaging, and fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.41,0:00:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's start.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.58,0:00:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First up is first Launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first experience
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.11,0:00:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,people have with your game and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.05,0:00:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,your first impression matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.85,0:00:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no matter what you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.09,0:00:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,say first, whether it is Accept
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.82,0:01:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Terms, or Headsets Recommended,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,design the first screen to fit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.28,0:01:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,within the style of your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.67,0:01:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, they're immersed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.79,0:01:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.22,0:01:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This edge to edge illustration
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.67,0:01:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,from Pokemon Go does a great
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.43,0:01:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,job, and it communicates just as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,much as the text on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.33,0:01:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, take the time to design what
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.27,0:01:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,people see first as soon as they
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.75,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,launch your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.16,0:01:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When this is done well, it'll
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.64,0:01:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,make a lasting impression and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.03,0:01:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,set the tone for the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.26,0:01:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.04,0:01:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is Loading because
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.09,0:01:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it takes just a few
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.53,0:01:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds to pull data through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.95,0:01:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why not take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.71,0:01:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what we all know to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.91,0:01:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,time flies when you're having
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.60,0:01:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, during Loading, make it fun
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.77,0:01:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by educating or entertaining;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.09,0:01:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,then, Loading won't see to take
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.62,0:01:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as long.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Don't Starve Pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.29,0:01:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Edition, and in this game
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.40,0:01:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Loading is masked by this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.77,0:01:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,beautifully creepy animation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.98,0:01:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,players are entertained, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.55,0:01:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,time seems to fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Loading is also a great time to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.55,0:02:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,educate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.57,0:02:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In Clash Royale, as you prepare
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.33,0:02:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for battle, a gameplay tip is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,shown on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you choose to do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that players have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.04,0:02:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,enough time to read the tip and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.37,0:02:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,also be intelligent about what
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.93,0:02:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you show people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone's already seen a tip,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.54,0:02:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,don't repeat it in the same
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, to show Loading
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,progress, always favor progress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,bars over activity indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because they do a much better
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.13,0:02:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,job communicating what's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,happening and how long it will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.95,0:02:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,take.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.08,0:02:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no matter when your game
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.16,0:02:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to load, entertain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.07,0:02:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,educate, and show progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.40,0:02:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, next is Quick Start.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.25,0:02:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Being able to start quickly and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.90,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,jump into your game is key to a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,great game experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.10,0:02:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is INKS, and it's an Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Design Award winner from last
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.36,0:02:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fun that you're able
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.72,0:02:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a feeling for the game
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.15,0:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,right from launch, but also they
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,do a great job making it obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.88,0:02:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to start the game with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:02:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,this large turquoise Play
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:02:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.57,0:03:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as you tap it, there
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.31,0:03:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are only two screens before
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.93,0:03:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in and playing the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.88,0:03:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which is awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.39,0:03:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let people get into your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,game easily and quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.61,0:03:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask players to make too
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,many choices before they
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.15,0:03:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,understand what it means in your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.71,0:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.16,0:03:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And for more complex games, I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,know there are important things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.96,0:03:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to show your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,players.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.25,0:03:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And game Main Menus have become
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,increasingly busy with news,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.17,0:03:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,tournaments, stores, and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And these can all be on your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.90,0:03:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, but make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.91,0:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the main call to action to play,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,start, battle, or begin a new
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.39,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,game is the most dominant in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your Main Menu UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, tip 4 is all about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.72,0:03:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our game's interface, and before
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we jump into this tip, you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,should know something about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's, I have a soft spot
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for classic arcade games.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this fake alien monster game
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.76,0:03:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to help us with a few
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.17,0:03:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,user interface best practices,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.08,0:04:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Consistency improves usability
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because it helps people mentally
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.54,0:04:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,map your interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.99,0:04:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much easier to play and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,navigate when controls are in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,predictable locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.16,0:04:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, be consistent in the layout
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.77,0:04:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of your game's menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, people can spend their
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,energy playing your game versus
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to recall where was that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.52,0:04:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings button.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's look at this exact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.35,0:04:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,same flow with an inconsistent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Back button is all over the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,place, and Settings disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Choose Character screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This inconsistency disrupts a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.94,0:04:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,player's experience because it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,takes more effort to mentally
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.69,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,map the interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.25,0:04:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're designing, to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate for consistency, lay
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,out all of your screens and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,check them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.03,0:04:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, you'll be able to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.43,0:04:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the controls are in the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.70,0:04:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.76,0:04:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. The next UI best practice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.11,0:04:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is all about clarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.39,0:05:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs to be clear to players
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.74,0:05:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what's interactive and what's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.10,0:05:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.84,0:05:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If people have to think too much
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about what to tap, they're going
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.94,0:05:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be taken out of your game's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, items that are tappable need
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.60,0:05:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to look different from items
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not tappable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the top center of this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.56,0:05:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, my Lives is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.02,0:05:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just status, but with this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,visual appearance, it could be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,confused for something that's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.47,0:05:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is common in a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,games, and there is an easy fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Make non-interactive elements
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.78,0:05:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,look different by using color
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.34,0:05:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and shape, like this or this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can remove and put status
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.84,0:05:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,items away from interactive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.29,0:05:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In your interface, for clarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important always to include
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,three visual states for buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.83,0:05:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and controls because a lack of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,visual feedback can confuse
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,players.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.97,0:05:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Be sure to use a Normal state to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.75,0:05:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,show people that something's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tappable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Use a Press state when something
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.99,0:05:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,has been tapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.49,0:05:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, use a Disabled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.07,0:05:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,state for control that's not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,currently active or enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.64,0:06:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Many developers struggle if they
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,should remove or hide a control
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if it cannot be activated, but
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.51,0:06:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do that, when it does pop
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.88,0:06:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,back it could be really
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.71,0:06:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,confusing to players, especially
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,if this happens during gameplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.32,0:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for a much better user
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, use a Disabled
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.54,0:06:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This lets people know the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.59,0:06:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,control's location and action
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.71,0:06:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be possible soon when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that control is enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.83,0:06:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that's interactive on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.35,0:06:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your game's interface meets the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.73,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,minimum tap targets on iOS which
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is 44 by 44 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.19,0:06:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your interface is a tool to make
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.06,0:06:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of your game's world, so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.24,0:06:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,make it consistent and clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.39,0:06:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, people will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.78,0:06:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,stay engaged in your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.11,0:06:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I hope you all enjoy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.82,0:06:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that fake alien monster game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.20,0:06:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll come back in a bit to help
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,us with a few other design tips.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.87,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already halfway through at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:06:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,number 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.07,0:06:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This tip and the next few are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.58,0:07:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,about game tutorials.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.72,0:07:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Successful tutorials teach
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.28,0:07:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,gradually and in context through
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,progressive disclosure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.06,0:07:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your tutorial should be made up
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.37,0:07:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of three basic parts that align
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to the core loop of your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, it might be that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.85,0:07:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to fight monsters to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.79,0:07:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,get some gold, and then buy some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.71,0:07:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff to fight more challenging
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But be sure, in your tutorial,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.69,0:07:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it stays to those three basic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.81,0:07:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have to keep, if you have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.58,0:07:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach about economy in your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,game, keep it simple because
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,remember you're teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.33,0:07:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody something brand new.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, avoid overwhelming people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and including information in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your tutorial that is not
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.60,0:07:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,essential to gameplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this, such as upgrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,tournaments, messages, and your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.83,0:07:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,store can all be discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,after your tutorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.37,0:07:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, in your tutorial it's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.01,0:07:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,really important to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:07:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,clear direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:07:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have characters in your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.93,0:08:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,game, it's pretty common to have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a character walk you through the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.35,0:08:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.86,0:08:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say we have this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.22,0:08:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,adorable alien monster, keep
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,directions short and simple to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.41,0:08:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,be effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.16,0:08:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, whether you teach with a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,character or through in-game
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,instructional text, a single
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,clear direction is going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the most effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.70,0:08:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And please, don't repeat
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.41,0:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect your players and treat,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.78,0:08:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't treat them like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.91,0:08:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.24,0:08:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if your players are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.57,0:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,children, kids are smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.42,0:08:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, repeating directions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.10,0:08:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,unnecessarily lengthens your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial, and that makes it less
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.03,0:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,effective and less fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.47,0:08:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And learning is really fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when the teacher is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,engaging, creative, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,inventive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.32,0:08:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, be the cool teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.11,0:08:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just do what you've seen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.57,0:08:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,others do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.66,0:08:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If your game is unique, your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.23,0:08:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial should be too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, think about how you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.17,0:08:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,can teach before your game
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.74,0:08:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Splitter Critters, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.51,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in this game you split the world
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with a swipe of your finger and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.17,0:09:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then rearrange it to guide
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.33,0:09:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,critters back to their
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.22,0:09:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the Start screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.87,0:09:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're taught this key game
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.22,0:09:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the least effective
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.44,0:09:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,ways to teach is with a bouncing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.41,0:09:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not effective because
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.31,0:09:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,people just end up playing tap
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the pointing arrow game and not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same goes for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.95,0:09:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,floating hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do you not learn, but
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this method is really
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.23,0:09:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,problematic because it hides you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.85,0:09:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,from the interface that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to be learning about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.20,0:09:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there are much better
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.71,0:09:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,attention-getting devices that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.14,0:09:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are way more natural and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,immersive, such as animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Reigns, and I was really
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.68,0:09:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,excited to hear that the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.74,0:09:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,developer is soon updating to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.50,0:09:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,remove the floating hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right, is the new
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,experience and, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.30,0:09:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's much more immersive; it's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.22,0:09:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,just as effective, and it does a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,great job getting you right into
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of Reigns.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And being in the world of your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,game is the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you can let people jump
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,right in and learn through play,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.85,0:10:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that is going to be the most
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.47,0:10:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,effective way to teach them your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.31,0:10:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.31,0:10:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is Mars: Mars on Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.64,0:10:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is really fun to be able
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to jump right into the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.21,0:10:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So right now, I'm on Mars, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.87,0:10:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the controls are intuitive, so
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.07,0:10:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to start clicking
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.89,0:10:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And after one hilarious death, I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.50,0:10:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly realize that the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.66,0:10:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,objective is to land safely on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for the best experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.54,0:10:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,teach people through play.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we're already at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.90,0:10:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,number 9, which is all about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,letting people skip and get
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.99,0:10:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,right into your game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.05,0:10:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give the player control, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.87,0:10:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that way Skip can create a much
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,better user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.98,0:10:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I love this opening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.32,0:11:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sequence from Icycle: On Thin
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.93,0:11:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clever, has a striking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.67,0:11:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,style, and it provides you with
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the motivation of the main
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.30,0:11:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,character, Dennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.37,0:11:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you tap on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a very subtle Skip button
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is great because
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.85,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,revealing Skip on tap is a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Players who are ready to jump
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,right into your game can, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.09,0:11:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,people who want to watch the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.27,0:11:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,entire sequence can stay
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,immersed with edge to edge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.98,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,playback.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, letting players Skip also
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.94,0:11:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,applies to tutorials.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Zombie Gunship, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.94,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the upper left-hand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.88,0:11:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.79,0:11:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a Skip Tutorial button,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.37,0:11:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it feels great to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,jump right into the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.98,0:11:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be sure if you allow people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.56,0:11:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to Skip your tutorial, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,able to relaunch or replay the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial in case they need a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.74,0:11:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,refresher on the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.38,0:11:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I understand that this may
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.32,0:11:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not work for every game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if it's critical to your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:11:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,game's progression to include a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:12:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial level, teach the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,basics, gradually adding context
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,through progressive disclosure,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.40,0:12:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then get out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting players Skip is about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.30,0:12:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,putting the player's experience
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.12,0:12:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,first because you don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.62,0:12:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,someone's skill level or how
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.12,0:12:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,much time they have to play your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.58,0:12:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure we have all button
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.42,0:12:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,smashed and clicked as quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.02,0:12:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as possible to get through a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,tutorial just to get into the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.65,0:12:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.77,0:12:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for a much better user
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.17,0:12:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, provide a Skip
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.79,0:12:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tutorial button.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.39,0:12:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, respect the player and that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,way, they will be able to have a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.56,0:12:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,much better user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.64,0:12:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The final design tip today is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.92,0:12:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,about being inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot that you can do to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.29,0:12:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,make your game more accessible,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.83,0:12:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,such as adding Closed Captions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.55,0:12:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or supporting Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.75,0:12:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also, just like in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.61,0:12:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushroom 11, support Left and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Right-Hand Mode, or you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.21,0:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,support Color Blind Mode, like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in KAMI 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the coolest
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.59,0:13:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility updates that I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.90,0:13:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,have seen is from Blackbox,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.33,0:13:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a visual puzzler that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.17,0:13:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,now includes sonic interfaces to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,let players with low or no
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.81,0:13:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,vision play through solving
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.33,0:13:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,puzzles with sound.
